45 static int32_t adjustUp(int32_t V, uint8_t A, uint8_t O) { 0
46 assert(isPowerOf2_32(A)); 0
47 int32_t U = (V & -A) + O; 0
48 return U >= V ? U : U+A; 0
49 } ----
50 ----
51 static int32_t adjustDown(int32_t V, uint8_t A, uint8_t O) { 0
52 assert(isPowerOf2_32(A)); 0
53 int32_t U = (V & -A) + O; 0
54 return U <= V ? U : U-A; 0
55 } ----

58 struct OffsetRange { ----
59 // The range of values between Min and Max that are of form Align*N+Offset, ----
60 // for some integer N. Min and Max are required to be of that form as well, ----
61 // except in the case of an empty range. ----
62 int32_t Min = INT_MIN, Max = INT_MAX; ----
63 uint8_t Align = 1; ----
64 uint8_t Offset = 0; ----
65 ----
66 OffsetRange() = default; 0
67 OffsetRange(int32_t L, int32_t H, uint8_t A, uint8_t O = 0) 0
68 : Min(L), Max(H), Align(A), Offset(O) {} 0
69 OffsetRange &intersect(OffsetRange A) { 0
70 if (Align < A.Align) 0
71 std::swap(*this, A); 0
72 ----
73 // Align >= A.Align. ----
74 if (Offset >= A.Offset && (Offset - A.Offset) % A.Align == 0) { 0
75 Min = adjustUp(std::max(Min, A.Min), Align, Offset); 0
76 Max = adjustDown(std::min(Max, A.Max), Align, Offset); 0
77 } else { ----
78 // Make an empty range. ----
79 Min = 0; 0
80 Max = -1; 0
81 } ----
82 // Canonicalize empty ranges. ----
83 if (Min > Max) 0
84 std::tie(Min, Max, Align) = std::make_tuple(0, -1, 1); 0
85 return *this; 0
86 } ----
87 OffsetRange &shift(int32_t S) { 0
88 Min += S; 0
89 Max += S; 0
90 Offset = (Offset+S) % Align; 0
91 return *this; 0
92 } ----
93 OffsetRange &extendBy(int32_t D) { 0
94 // If D < 0, extend Min, otherwise extend Max. ----
95 assert(D % Align == 0); 0
96 if (D < 0) 0
97 Min = (INT_MIN-D < Min) ? Min+D : INT_MIN; 0
98 else ----
99 Max = (INT_MAX-D > Max) ? Max+D : INT_MAX; 0
100 return *this; 0
101 } ----
102 bool empty() const { ----
103 return Min > Max; ----
104 } ----
105 bool contains(int32_t V) const { 0
106 return Min <= V && V <= Max && (V-Offset) % Align == 0; 0
107 } ----
108 bool operator==(const OffsetRange &R) const { 0
109 return Min == R.Min && Max == R.Max && Align == R.Align; 0
110 } ----
111 bool operator!=(const OffsetRange &R) const { 0
112 return !operator==(R); 0
113 } ----
114 bool operator<(const OffsetRange &R) const { 0
115 if (Min != R.Min) 0
116 return Min < R.Min; 0
117 if (Max != R.Max) 0
118 return Max < R.Max; 0
119 return Align < R.Align; 0
120 } ----
121 static OffsetRange zero() { return {0, 0, 1}; } 0
122 }; ----

172 Node *update(Node *N) { 0
173 assert(N != nullptr); 0
174 N->Height = 1 + std::max(height(N->Left), height(N->Right)); 0
175 if (N->Left) 0
176 N->MaxEnd = std::max(N->MaxEnd, N->Left->MaxEnd); 0
177 if (N->Right) 0
178 N->MaxEnd = std::max(N->MaxEnd, N->Right->MaxEnd); 0
179 return N; 0
180 } ----
181 Node *rebalance(Node *N) { 0
182 assert(N != nullptr); 0
183 int32_t Balance = height(N->Right) - height(N->Left); 0
184 if (Balance < -1) 0
185 return rotateRight(N->Left, N); 0
186 if (Balance > 1) 0
187 return rotateLeft(N->Right, N); 0
188 return N; 0
189 } ----

271 struct ExtExpr { ----
272 // A subexpression in which the extender is used. In general, this ----
273 // represents an expression where adding D to the extender will be ----
274 // equivalent to adding D to the expression as a whole. In other ----
275 // words, expr(add(##V,D) = add(expr(##V),D). ----
276 ----
277 // The original motivation for this are the io/ur addressing modes, ----
278 // where the offset is extended. Consider the io example: ----
279 // In memw(Rs+##V), the ##V could be replaced by a register Rt to ----
280 // form the rr mode: memw(Rt+Rs<<0). In such case, however, the ----
281 // register Rt must have exactly the value of ##V. If there was ----
282 // another instruction memw(Rs+##V+4), it would need a different Rt. ----
283 // Now, if Rt was initialized as "##V+Rs<<0", both of these ----
284 // instructions could use the same Rt, just with different offsets. ----
285 // Here it's clear that "initializer+4" should be the same as if ----
286 // the offset 4 was added to the ##V in the initializer. ----
287 ----
288 // The only kinds of expressions that support the requirement of ----
289 // commuting with addition are addition and subtraction from ##V. ----
290 // Include shifting the Rs to account for the ur addressing mode: ----
291 // ##Val + Rs << S ----
292 // ##Val - Rs ----
293 Register Rs; ----
294 unsigned S = 0; ----
295 bool Neg = false; ----
296 ----
297 ExtExpr() = default; 0
298 ExtExpr(Register RS, bool NG, unsigned SH) : Rs(RS), S(SH), Neg(NG) {} ----
299 // Expression is trivial if it does not modify the extender. ----
300 bool trivial() const { 0
301 return Rs.Reg == 0; 0
302 } ----
303 bool operator==(const ExtExpr &Ex) const { ----
304 return Rs == Ex.Rs && S == Ex.S && Neg == Ex.Neg; ----
305 } ----
306 bool operator!=(const ExtExpr &Ex) const { ----
307 return !operator==(Ex); ----
308 } ----
309 bool operator<(const ExtExpr &Ex) const { 0
310 if (Rs != Ex.Rs) 0
311 return Rs < Ex.Rs; 0
312 if (S != Ex.S) 0
313 return S < Ex.S; 0
314 return !Neg && Ex.Neg; 0
315 } ----
316 }; ----

603 void RangeTree::order(Node *N, SmallVectorImpl &Seq) const { 0
604 if (N == nullptr) 0
605 return; 0
606 order(N->Left, Seq); 0
607 Seq.push_back(N); 0
608 order(N->Right, Seq); 0
609 } ----
610 ----
611 void RangeTree::nodesWith(Node *N, int32_t P, bool CheckA, 0
612 SmallVectorImpl &Seq) const { ----
613 if (N == nullptr || N->MaxEnd < P) 0
614 return; 0
615 nodesWith(N->Left, P, CheckA, Seq); 0
616 if (N->Range.Min <= P) { 0
617 if ((CheckA && N->Range.contains(P)) || (!CheckA && P <= N->Range.Max)) 0
618 Seq.push_back(N); 0
619 nodesWith(N->Right, P, CheckA, Seq); 0
620 } ----
621 } ----
622 ----
623 RangeTree::Node *RangeTree::add(Node *N, const OffsetRange &R) { 0
624 if (N == nullptr) 0
625 return new Node(R); 0
626 ----
627 if (N->Range == R) { 0
628 N->Count++; 0
629 return N; 0
630 } ----
631 ----
632 if (R < N->Range) 0
633 N->Left = add(N->Left, R); 0
634 else ----
635 N->Right = add(N->Right, R); 0
636 return rebalance(update(N)); 0
637 } ----
638 ----
639 RangeTree::Node *RangeTree::remove(Node *N, const Node *D) { 0
640 assert(N != nullptr); 0
641 ----
642 if (N != D) { 0
643 assert(N->Range != D->Range && "N and D should not be equal"); 0
644 if (D->Range < N->Range) 0
645 N->Left = remove(N->Left, D); 0
646 else ----
647 N->Right = remove(N->Right, D); 0
648 return rebalance(update(N)); 0
649 } ----
650 ----
651 // We got to the node we need to remove. If any of its children are ----
652 // missing, simply replace it with the other child. ----
653 if (N->Left == nullptr || N->Right == nullptr) 0
654 return (N->Left == nullptr) ? N->Right : N->Left; 0
655 ----
656 // Find the rightmost child of N->Left, remove it and plug it in place ----
657 // of N. ----
658 Node *M = N->Left; 0
659 while (M->Right) 0
660 M = M->Right; 0
661 M->Left = remove(N->Left, M); 0
662 M->Right = N->Right; 0
663 return rebalance(update(M)); 0
664 } ----
665 ----
666 RangeTree::Node *RangeTree::rotateLeft(Node *Lower, Node *Higher) { 0
667 assert(Higher->Right == Lower); 0
668 // The Lower node is on the right from Higher. Make sure that Lower's ----
669 // balance is greater to the right. Otherwise the rotation will create ----
670 // an unbalanced tree again. ----
671 if (height(Lower->Left) > height(Lower->Right)) 0
672 Lower = rotateRight(Lower->Left, Lower); 0
673 assert(height(Lower->Left) <= height(Lower->Right)); 0
674 Higher->Right = Lower->Left; 0
675 update(Higher); 0
676 Lower->Left = Higher; 0
677 update(Lower); 0
678 return Lower; 0
679 } ----
680 ----
681 RangeTree::Node *RangeTree::rotateRight(Node *Lower, Node *Higher) { 0
682 assert(Higher->Left == Lower); 0
683 // The Lower node is on the left from Higher. Make sure that Lower's ----
684 // balance is greater to the left. Otherwise the rotation will create ----
685 // an unbalanced tree again. ----
686 if (height(Lower->Left) < height(Lower->Right)) 0
687 Lower = rotateLeft(Lower->Right, Lower); 0
688 assert(height(Lower->Left) >= height(Lower->Right)); 0
689 Higher->Left = Lower->Right; 0
690 update(Higher); 0
691 Lower->Right = Higher; 0
692 update(Lower); 0
693 return Lower; 0
694 } ----
695 ----
696 ----
697 HCE::ExtRoot::ExtRoot(const MachineOperand &Op) { 0
698 // Always store ImmVal, since it's the field used for comparisons. ----
699 V.ImmVal = 0; 0
700 if (Op.isImm()) 0
701 ; // Keep 0. Do not use Op.getImm() for value here (treat 0 as the root). ----
702 else if (Op.isFPImm()) 0
703 V.CFP = Op.getFPImm(); 0
704 else if (Op.isSymbol()) 0
705 V.SymbolName = Op.getSymbolName(); 0
706 else if (Op.isGlobal()) 0
707 V.GV = Op.getGlobal(); 0
708 else if (Op.isBlockAddress()) 0
709 V.BA = Op.getBlockAddress(); 0
710 else if (Op.isCPI() || Op.isTargetIndex() || Op.isJTI()) 0
711 V.ImmVal = Op.getIndex(); 0
712 else ----
713 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected operand type"); 0
714 ----
715 Kind = Op.getType(); 0
716 TF = Op.getTargetFlags(); 0
717 } 0
718 ----
719 bool HCE::ExtRoot::operator< (const HCE::ExtRoot &ER) const { 0
720 if (Kind != ER.Kind) 0
721 return Kind < ER.Kind; 0
722 switch (Kind) { 0
723 case MachineOperand::MO_Immediate: 0
724 case MachineOperand::MO_TargetIndex: ----
725 case MachineOperand::MO_ConstantPoolIndex: ----
726 case MachineOperand::MO_JumpTableIndex: ----
727 return V.ImmVal < ER.V.ImmVal; 0
728 case MachineOperand::MO_FPImmediate: { 0
729 const APFloat &ThisF = V.CFP->getValueAPF(); 0
730 const APFloat &OtherF = ER.V.CFP->getValueAPF(); 0
731 return ThisF.bitcastToAPInt().ult(OtherF.bitcastToAPInt()); 0
732 } ----
733 case MachineOperand::MO_ExternalSymbol: 0
734 return StringRef(V.SymbolName) < StringRef(ER.V.SymbolName); 0
735 case MachineOperand::MO_GlobalAddress: 0
736 // Do not use GUIDs, since they depend on the source path. Moving the ----
737 // source file to a different directory could cause different GUID ----
738 // values for a pair of given symbols. These symbols could then compare ----
739 // "less" in one directory, but "greater" in another. ----
740 assert(!V.GV->getName().empty() && !ER.V.GV->getName().empty()); 0
741 return V.GV->getName() < ER.V.GV->getName(); 0
742 case MachineOperand::MO_BlockAddress: { 0
743 const BasicBlock *ThisB = V.BA->getBasicBlock(); 0
744 const BasicBlock *OtherB = ER.V.BA->getBasicBlock(); 0
745 assert(ThisB->getParent() == OtherB->getParent()); 0
746 const Function &F = *ThisB->getParent(); 0
747 return std::distance(F.begin(), ThisB->getIterator()) < 0
748 std::distance(F.begin(), OtherB->getIterator()); 0
749 } ----
750 } ----
751 return V.ImmVal < ER.V.ImmVal; 0
752 } ----
753 ----
754 HCE::ExtValue::ExtValue(const MachineOperand &Op) : ExtRoot(Op) { 0
755 if (Op.isImm()) 0
756 Offset = Op.getImm(); 0
757 else if (Op.isFPImm() || Op.isJTI()) 0
758 Offset = 0; 0
759 else if (Op.isSymbol() || Op.isGlobal() || Op.isBlockAddress() || 0
760 Op.isCPI() || Op.isTargetIndex()) 0
761 Offset = Op.getOffset(); 0
762 else ----
763 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected operand type"); 0
764 } 0
765 ----
766 bool HCE::ExtValue::operator< (const HCE::ExtValue &EV) const { 0
767 const ExtRoot &ER = *this; 0
768 if (!(ER == ExtRoot(EV))) 0
769 return ER < EV; 0
770 return Offset < EV.Offset; 0
771 } ----
772 ----
773 HCE::ExtValue::operator MachineOperand() const { 0
774 switch (Kind) { 0
775 case MachineOperand::MO_Immediate: 0
776 return MachineOperand::CreateImm(V.ImmVal + Offset); 0
777 case MachineOperand::MO_FPImmediate: 0
778 assert(Offset == 0); 0
779 return MachineOperand::CreateFPImm(V.CFP); 0
780 case MachineOperand::MO_ExternalSymbol: 0
781 assert(Offset == 0); 0
782 return MachineOperand::CreateES(V.SymbolName, TF); 0
783 case MachineOperand::MO_GlobalAddress: 0
784 return MachineOperand::CreateGA(V.GV, Offset, TF); 0
785 case MachineOperand::MO_BlockAddress: 0
786 return MachineOperand::CreateBA(V.BA, Offset, TF); 0
787 case MachineOperand::MO_TargetIndex: 0
788 return MachineOperand::CreateTargetIndex(V.ImmVal, Offset, TF); 0
789 case MachineOperand::MO_ConstantPoolIndex: 0
790 return MachineOperand::CreateCPI(V.ImmVal, Offset, TF); 0
791 case MachineOperand::MO_JumpTableIndex: 0
792 assert(Offset == 0); 0
793 return MachineOperand::CreateJTI(V.ImmVal, TF); 0
794 default: 0
795 llvm_unreachable("Unhandled kind"); 0
796 } ----
797 } ----

966 unsigned HCE::getDirectRegReplacement(unsigned ExtOpc) const { 0
967 switch (ExtOpc) { 0
968 case Hexagon::A2_addi: return Hexagon::A2_add; 0

971 case Hexagon::A2_orir: return Hexagon::A2_or; 0
972 case Hexagon::A2_paddif: return Hexagon::A2_paddf; 0
973 case Hexagon::A2_paddit: return Hexagon::A2_paddt; 0
974 case Hexagon::A2_subri: return Hexagon::A2_sub; 0
975 case Hexagon::A2_tfrsi: return TargetOpcode::COPY; 0
976 case Hexagon::A4_cmpbeqi: return Hexagon::A4_cmpbeq; 0
977 case Hexagon::A4_cmpbgti: return Hexagon::A4_cmpbgt; 0
978 case Hexagon::A4_cmpbgtui: return Hexagon::A4_cmpbgtu; 0
979 case Hexagon::A4_cmpheqi: return Hexagon::A4_cmpheq; 0
980 case Hexagon::A4_cmphgti: return Hexagon::A4_cmphgt; 0
981 case Hexagon::A4_cmphgtui: return Hexagon::A4_cmphgtu; 0
982 case Hexagon::A4_combineii: return Hexagon::A4_combineir; 0
983 case Hexagon::A4_combineir: return TargetOpcode::REG_SEQUENCE; 0
984 case Hexagon::A4_combineri: return TargetOpcode::REG_SEQUENCE; 0
985 case Hexagon::A4_rcmpeqi: return Hexagon::A4_rcmpeq; 0
986 case Hexagon::A4_rcmpneqi: return Hexagon::A4_rcmpneq; 0
987 case Hexagon::C2_cmoveif: return Hexagon::A2_tfrpf; 0
988 case Hexagon::C2_cmoveit: return Hexagon::A2_tfrpt; 0
989 case Hexagon::C2_cmpeqi: return Hexagon::C2_cmpeq; 0
990 case Hexagon::C2_cmpgti: return Hexagon::C2_cmpgt; 0
991 case Hexagon::C2_cmpgtui: return Hexagon::C2_cmpgtu; 0
992 case Hexagon::C2_muxii: return Hexagon::C2_muxir; 0
993 case Hexagon::C2_muxir: return Hexagon::C2_mux; 0
994 case Hexagon::C2_muxri: return Hexagon::C2_mux; 0
995 case Hexagon::C4_cmpltei: return Hexagon::C4_cmplte; 0
996 case Hexagon::C4_cmplteui: return Hexagon::C4_cmplteu; 0
997 case Hexagon::C4_cmpneqi: return Hexagon::C4_cmpneq; 0
998 case Hexagon::M2_accii: return Hexagon::M2_acci; // T -> T 0
999 /* No M2_macsin */ ----
1000 case Hexagon::M2_macsip: return Hexagon::M2_maci; // T -> T 0
1001 case Hexagon::M2_mpysin: return Hexagon::M2_mpyi; 0
1002 case Hexagon::M2_mpysip: return Hexagon::M2_mpyi; 0
1003 case Hexagon::M2_mpysmi: return Hexagon::M2_mpyi; 0
1004 case Hexagon::M2_naccii: return Hexagon::M2_nacci; // T -> T 0
1005 case Hexagon::M4_mpyri_addi: return Hexagon::M4_mpyri_addr; 0

1012 case Hexagon::S4_andi_lsr_ri: return Hexagon::S2_lsr_i_r_and; // T -> T 0
1013 case Hexagon::S4_ori_asl_ri: return Hexagon::S2_asl_i_r_or; // T -> T 0
1014 case Hexagon::S4_ori_lsr_ri: return Hexagon::S2_lsr_i_r_or; // T -> T 0

1016 case Hexagon::S4_subi_asl_ri: return Hexagon::S2_asl_i_r_nac; // T -> T 0
1017 case Hexagon::S4_subi_lsr_ri: return Hexagon::S2_lsr_i_r_nac; // T -> T 0
1018 ----
1019 // Store-immediates: ----
1020 case Hexagon::S4_storeirbf_io: return Hexagon::S2_pstorerbf_io; 0
1021 case Hexagon::S4_storeirb_io: return Hexagon::S2_storerb_io; 0
1022 case Hexagon::S4_storeirbt_io: return Hexagon::S2_pstorerbt_io; 0
1023 case Hexagon::S4_storeirhf_io: return Hexagon::S2_pstorerhf_io; 0
1024 case Hexagon::S4_storeirh_io: return Hexagon::S2_storerh_io; 0
1025 case Hexagon::S4_storeirht_io: return Hexagon::S2_pstorerht_io; 0
1026 case Hexagon::S4_storeirif_io: return Hexagon::S2_pstorerif_io; 0
1027 case Hexagon::S4_storeiri_io: return Hexagon::S2_storeri_io; 0
1028 case Hexagon::S4_storeirit_io: return Hexagon::S2_pstorerit_io; 0
1029 ----
1030 default: 0
1031 break; 0
1032 } ----
1033 return 0; 0
1034 } ----
1035 ----
1036 // Return the allowable deviation from the current value of Rb (i.e. the ----
1037 // range of values that can be added to the current value) which the ----
1038 // instruction MI can accommodate. ----
1039 // The instruction MI is a user of register Rb, which is defined via an ----
1040 // extender. It may be possible for MI to be tweaked to work for a register ----
1041 // defined with a slightly different value. For example ----
1042 // ... = L2_loadrub_io Rb, 1 ----
1043 // can be modifed to be ----
1044 // ... = L2_loadrub_io Rb', 0 ----
1045 // if Rb' = Rb+1. ----
1046 // The range for Rb would be [Min+1, Max+1], where [Min, Max] is a range ----
1047 // for L2_loadrub with offset 0. That means that Rb could be replaced with ----
1048 // Rc, where Rc-Rb belongs to [Min+1, Max+1]. ----
1049 OffsetRange HCE::getOffsetRange(Register Rb, const MachineInstr &MI) const { 0
1050 unsigned Opc = MI.getOpcode(); 0
1051 // Instructions that are constant-extended may be replaced with something ----
1052 // else that no longer offers the same range as the original. ----
1053 if (!isRegOffOpcode(Opc) || HII->isConstExtended(MI)) 0
1054 return OffsetRange::zero(); 0
1055 ----
1056 if (Opc == Hexagon::A2_addi) { 0
1057 const MachineOperand &Op1 = MI.getOperand(1), &Op2 = MI.getOperand(2); 0
1058 if (Rb != Register(Op1) || !Op2.isImm()) 0
1059 return OffsetRange::zero(); 0
1060 OffsetRange R = { -(1<<15)+1, (1<<15)-1, 1 }; 0
1061 return R.shift(Op2.getImm()); 0
1062 } ----
1063 ----
1064 // HII::getBaseAndOffsetPosition returns the increment position as "offset". ----
1065 if (HII->isPostIncrement(MI)) 0
1066 return OffsetRange::zero(); 0
1067 ----
1068 const MCInstrDesc &D = HII->get(Opc); 0
1069 assert(D.mayLoad() || D.mayStore()); 0
1070 ----
1071 unsigned BaseP, OffP; ----
1072 if (!HII->getBaseAndOffsetPosition(MI, BaseP, OffP) || 0
1073 Rb != Register(MI.getOperand(BaseP)) || 0
1074 !MI.getOperand(OffP).isImm()) 0
1075 return OffsetRange::zero(); 0
1076 ----
1077 uint64_t F = (D.TSFlags >> HexagonII::MemAccessSizePos) & 0
1078 HexagonII::MemAccesSizeMask; ----
1079 uint8_t A = HexagonII::getMemAccessSizeInBytes(HexagonII::MemAccessSize(F)); 0
1080 unsigned L = Log2_32(A); 0
1081 unsigned S = 10+L; // sint11_L 0
1082 int32_t Min = -alignDown((1< 0
1083 ----
1084 // The range will be shifted by Off. To prefer non-negative offsets, ----
1085 // adjust Max accordingly. ----
1086 int32_t Off = MI.getOperand(OffP).getImm(); 0
1087 int32_t Max = Off >= 0 ? 0 : -Off; 0
1088 ----
1089 OffsetRange R = { Min, Max, A }; 0
1090 return R.shift(Off); 0
1091 } ----
1092 ----
1093 // Return the allowable deviation from the current value of the extender ED, ----
1094 // for which the instruction corresponding to ED can be modified without ----
1095 // using an extender. ----
1096 // The instruction uses the extender directly. It will be replaced with ----
1097 // another instruction, say MJ, where the extender will be replaced with a ----
1098 // register. MJ can allow some variability with respect to the value of ----
1099 // that register, as is the case with indexed memory instructions. ----
1100 OffsetRange HCE::getOffsetRange(const ExtDesc &ED) const { 0
1101 // The only way that there can be a non-zero range available is if ----
1102 // the instruction using ED will be converted to an indexed memory ----
1103 // instruction. ----
1104 unsigned IdxOpc = getRegOffOpcode(ED.UseMI->getOpcode()); 0
1105 switch (IdxOpc) { 0
1106 case 0: 0
1107 return OffsetRange::zero(); 0
1108 case Hexagon::A2_addi: // s16 0
1109 return { -32767, 32767, 1 }; 0
1110 case Hexagon::A2_subri: // s10 0
1111 return { -511, 511, 1 }; 0
1112 } ----
1113 ----
1114 if (!ED.UseMI->mayLoad() && !ED.UseMI->mayStore()) 0
1115 return OffsetRange::zero(); 0
1116 const MCInstrDesc &D = HII->get(IdxOpc); 0
1117 uint64_t F = (D.TSFlags >> HexagonII::MemAccessSizePos) & 0
1118 HexagonII::MemAccesSizeMask; ----
1119 uint8_t A = HexagonII::getMemAccessSizeInBytes(HexagonII::MemAccessSize(F)); 0
1120 unsigned L = Log2_32(A); 0
1121 unsigned S = 10+L; // sint11_L 0
1122 int32_t Min = -alignDown((1< 0
1123 int32_t Max = 0; // Force non-negative offsets. 0
1124 return { Min, Max, A }; 0
1125 } ----
1126 ----
1127 // Get the allowable deviation from the current value of Rd by checking ----
1128 // all uses of Rd. ----
1129 OffsetRange HCE::getOffsetRange(Register Rd) const { 0
1130 OffsetRange Range; 0
1131 for (const MachineOperand &Op : MRI->use_operands(Rd.Reg)) { 0
1132 // Make sure that the register being used by this operand is identical ----
1133 // to the register that was defined: using a different subregister ----
1134 // precludes any non-trivial range. ----
1135 if (Rd != Register(Op)) 0
1136 return OffsetRange::zero(); 0
1137 Range.intersect(getOffsetRange(Rd, *Op.getParent())); 0
1138 } ----
1139 return Range; 0
1140 } ----
1141 ----
1142 void HCE::recordExtender(MachineInstr &MI, unsigned OpNum) { 0
1143 unsigned Opc = MI.getOpcode(); 0
1144 ExtDesc ED; 0
1145 ED.OpNum = OpNum; 0
1146 ----
1147 bool IsLoad = MI.mayLoad(); 0
1148 bool IsStore = MI.mayStore(); 0
1149 ----
1150 // Fixed stack slots have negative indexes, and they cannot be used ----
1151 // with TRI::stackSlot2Index and TRI::index2StackSlot. This is somewhat ----
1152 // unfortunate, but should not be a frequent thing. ----
1153 for (MachineOperand &Op : MI.operands()) 0
1154 if (Op.isFI() && Op.getIndex() < 0) 0
1155 return; 0
1156 ----
1157 if (IsLoad || IsStore) { 0
1158 unsigned AM = HII->getAddrMode(MI); 0
1159 switch (AM) { 0
1160 // (Re: ##Off + Rb< ----
1161 case HexagonII::Absolute: // (__: ## + __<<_) 0
1162 break; 0
1163 case HexagonII::AbsoluteSet: // (Rd: ## + __<<_) 0
1164 ED.Rd = MI.getOperand(OpNum-1); 0
1165 ED.IsDef = true; 0
1166 break; 0
1167 case HexagonII::BaseImmOffset: // (__: ## + Rs<<0) 0
1168 // Store-immediates are treated as non-memory operations, since ----
1169 // it's the value being stored that is extended (as opposed to ----
1170 // a part of the address). ----
1171 if (!isStoreImmediate(Opc)) 0
1172 ED.Expr.Rs = MI.getOperand(OpNum-1); 0
1173 break; 0
1174 case HexagonII::BaseLongOffset: // (__: ## + Rs< 0
1175 ED.Expr.Rs = MI.getOperand(OpNum-2); 0
1176 ED.Expr.S = MI.getOperand(OpNum-1).getImm(); 0
1177 break; 0
1178 default: 0
1179 llvm_unreachable("Unhandled memory instruction"); 0
1180 } ----
1181 } else { 0
1182 switch (Opc) { 0
1183 case Hexagon::A2_tfrsi: // (Rd: ## + __<<_) 0
1184 ED.Rd = MI.getOperand(0); 0
1185 ED.IsDef = true; 0
1186 break; 0
1187 case Hexagon::A2_combineii: // (Rd: ## + __<<_) 0
1188 case Hexagon::A4_combineir: ----
1189 ED.Rd = { MI.getOperand(0).getReg(), Hexagon::isub_hi }; 0
1190 ED.IsDef = true; 0
1191 break; 0
1192 case Hexagon::A4_combineri: // (Rd: ## + __<<_) 0
1193 ED.Rd = { MI.getOperand(0).getReg(), Hexagon::isub_lo }; 0
1194 ED.IsDef = true; 0
1195 break; 0
1196 case Hexagon::A2_addi: // (Rd: ## + Rs<<0) 0
1197 ED.Rd = MI.getOperand(0); 0
1198 ED.Expr.Rs = MI.getOperand(OpNum-1); 0
1199 break; 0
1200 case Hexagon::M2_accii: // (__: ## + Rs<<0) 0
1201 case Hexagon::M2_naccii: ----
1202 case Hexagon::S4_addaddi: ----
1203 ED.Expr.Rs = MI.getOperand(OpNum-1); 0
1204 break; 0
1205 case Hexagon::A2_subri: // (Rd: ## - Rs<<0) 0
1206 ED.Rd = MI.getOperand(0); 0
1207 ED.Expr.Rs = MI.getOperand(OpNum+1); 0
1208 ED.Expr.Neg = true; 0
1209 break; 0
1210 case Hexagon::S4_subaddi: // (__: ## - Rs<<0) 0
1211 ED.Expr.Rs = MI.getOperand(OpNum+1); 0
1212 ED.Expr.Neg = true; 0
1213 break; 0
1214 default: // (__: ## + __<<_) 0
1215 break; 0
1216 } ----
1217 } ----
1218 ----
1219 ED.UseMI = &MI; 0
1220 ----
1221 // Ignore unnamed globals. ----
1222 ExtRoot ER(ED.getOp()); 0
1223 if (ER.Kind == MachineOperand::MO_GlobalAddress) 0
1224 if (ER.V.GV->getName().empty()) 0
1225 return; 0
1226 Extenders.push_back(ED); 0
1227 } ----
1228 ----
1229 void HCE::collectInstr(MachineInstr &MI) { 0
1230 if (!HII->isConstExtended(MI)) 0
1231 return; 0
1232 ----
1233 // Skip some non-convertible instructions. ----
1234 unsigned Opc = MI.getOpcode(); 0
1235 switch (Opc) { 0
1236 case Hexagon::M2_macsin: // There is no Rx -= mpyi(Rs,Rt). 0
1237 case Hexagon::C4_addipc: ----
1238 case Hexagon::S4_or_andi: ----
1239 case Hexagon::S4_or_andix: ----
1240 case Hexagon::S4_or_ori: ----
1241 return; 0
1242 } ----
1243 recordExtender(MI, HII->getCExtOpNum(MI)); 0
1244 } ----
1245 ----
1246 void HCE::collect(MachineFunction &MF) { 0
1247 Extenders.clear(); 0
1248 for (MachineBasicBlock &MBB : MF) { 0
1249 // Skip unreachable blocks. ----
1250 if (MBB.getNumber() == -1) 0
1251 continue; 0
1252 for (MachineInstr &MI : MBB) 0
1253 collectInstr(MI); 0
1254 } ----
1255 } 0
1256 ----
1257 void HCE::assignInits(const ExtRoot &ER, unsigned Begin, unsigned End, 0
1258 AssignmentMap &IMap) { ----
1259 // Basic correctness: make sure that all extenders in the range [Begin..End) ----
1260 // share the same root ER. ----
1261 for (unsigned I = Begin; I != End; ++I) 0
1262 assert(ER == ExtRoot(Extenders[I].getOp())); 0
1263 ----
1264 // Construct the list of ranges, such that for each P in Ranges[I], ----
1265 // a register Reg = ER+P can be used in place of Extender[I]. If the ----
1266 // instruction allows, uses in the form of Reg+Off are considered ----
1267 // (here, Off = required_value - P). ----
1268 std::vector Ranges(End-Begin); 0
1269 ----
1270 // For each extender that is a def, visit all uses of the defined register, ----
1271 // and produce an offset range that works for all uses. The def doesn't ----
1272 // have to be checked, because it can become dead if all uses can be updated ----
1273 // to use a different reg/offset. ----
1274 for (unsigned I = Begin; I != End; ++I) { 0
1275 const ExtDesc &ED = Extenders[I]; 0
1276 if (!ED.IsDef) 0
1277 continue; 0
1278 ExtValue EV(ED); 0
1279 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " =" << I << ". " << EV << " " << ED << '\n'); 0
1280 assert(ED.Rd.Reg != 0); 0
1281 Ranges[I-Begin] = getOffsetRange(ED.Rd).shift(EV.Offset); 0
1282 // A2_tfrsi is a special case: it will be replaced with A2_addi, which ----
1283 // has a 16-bit signed offset. This means that A2_tfrsi not only has a ----
1284 // range coming from its uses, but also from the fact that its replacement ----
1285 // has a range as well. ----
1286 if (ED.UseMI->getOpcode() == Hexagon::A2_tfrsi) { 0
1287 int32_t D = alignDown(32767, Ranges[I-Begin].Align); // XXX hardcoded 0
1288 Ranges[I-Begin].extendBy(-D).extendBy(D); 0
1289 } ----
1290 } ----
1291 ----
1292 // Visit all non-def extenders. For each one, determine the offset range ----
1293 // available for it. ----
1294 for (unsigned I = Begin; I != End; ++I) { 0
1295 const ExtDesc &ED = Extenders[I]; 0
1296 if (ED.IsDef) 0
1297 continue; 0
1298 ExtValue EV(ED); 0
1299 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " " << I << ". " << EV << " " << ED << '\n'); 0
1300 OffsetRange Dev = getOffsetRange(ED); 0
1301 Ranges[I-Begin].intersect(Dev.shift(EV.Offset)); 0
1302 } ----
1303 ----
1304 // Here for each I there is a corresponding Range[I]. Construct the ----
1305 // inverse map, that to each range will assign the set of indexes in ----
1306 // [Begin..End) that this range corresponds to. ----
1307 std::map RangeMap; 0
1308 for (unsigned I = Begin; I != End; ++I) 0
1309 RangeMap[Ranges[I-Begin]].insert(I); 0
1310 ----
1311 LLVM_DEBUG({ 0
1312 dbgs() << "Ranges\n"; ----
1313 for (unsigned I = Begin; I != End; ++I) ----
1314 dbgs() << " " << I << ". " << Ranges[I-Begin] << '\n'; ----
1315 dbgs() << "RangeMap\n"; ----
1316 for (auto &P : RangeMap) { ----
1317 dbgs() << " " << P.first << " ->"; ----
1318 for (unsigned I : P.second) ----
1319 dbgs() << ' ' << I; ----
1320 dbgs() << '\n'; ----
1321 } ----
1322 }); ----
1323 ----
1324 // Select the definition points, and generate the assignment between ----
1325 // these points and the uses. ----
1326 ----
1327 // For each candidate offset, keep a pair CandData consisting of ----
1328 // the total number of ranges containing that candidate, and the ----
1329 // vector of corresponding RangeTree nodes. ----
1330 using CandData = std::pair>; ----
1331 std::map CandMap; 0
1332 ----
1333 RangeTree Tree; 0
1334 for (const OffsetRange &R : Ranges) 0
1335 Tree.add(R); 0
1336 SmallVector Nodes; 0
1337 Tree.order(Nodes); 0
1338 ----
1339 auto MaxAlign = [](const SmallVectorImpl &Nodes, 0
1340 uint8_t Align, uint8_t Offset) { ----
1341 for (RangeTree::Node *N : Nodes) { 0
1342 if (N->Range.Align <= Align || N->Range.Offset < Offset) 0
1343 continue; 0
1344 if ((N->Range.Offset - Offset) % Align != 0) 0
1345 continue; 0
1346 Align = N->Range.Align; 0
1347 Offset = N->Range.Offset; 0
1348 } ----
1349 return std::make_pair(Align, Offset); 0
1350 }; ----
1351 ----
1352 // Construct the set of all potential definition points from the endpoints ----
1353 // of the ranges. If a given endpoint also belongs to a different range, ----
1354 // but with a higher alignment, also consider the more-highly-aligned ----
1355 // value of this endpoint. ----
1356 std::set CandSet; 0
1357 for (RangeTree::Node *N : Nodes) { 0
1358 const OffsetRange &R = N->Range; 0
1359 auto P0 = MaxAlign(Tree.nodesWith(R.Min, false), R.Align, R.Offset); 0
1360 CandSet.insert(R.Min); 0
1361 if (R.Align < P0.first) 0
1362 CandSet.insert(adjustUp(R.Min, P0.first, P0.second)); 0
1363 auto P1 = MaxAlign(Tree.nodesWith(R.Max, false), R.Align, R.Offset); 0
1364 CandSet.insert(R.Max); 0
1365 if (R.Align < P1.first) 0
1366 CandSet.insert(adjustDown(R.Max, P1.first, P1.second)); 0
1367 } ----
1368 ----
1369 // Build the assignment map: candidate C -> { list of extender indexes }. ----
1370 // This has to be done iteratively: ----
1371 // - pick the candidate that covers the maximum number of extenders, ----
1372 // - add the candidate to the map, ----
1373 // - remove the extenders from the pool. ----
1374 while (true) { ----
1375 using CMap = std::map; ----
1376 CMap Counts; 0
1377 for (auto It = CandSet.begin(), Et = CandSet.end(); It != Et; ) { 0
1378 auto &&V = Tree.nodesWith(*It); 0
1379 unsigned N = std::accumulate(V.begin(), V.end(), 0u, 0
1380 [](unsigned Acc, const RangeTree::Node *N) { 0
1381 return Acc + N->Count; 0
1382 }); 0
1383 if (N != 0) 0
1384 Counts.insert({*It, N}); 0
1385 It = (N != 0) ? std::next(It) : CandSet.erase(It); 0
1386 } 0
1387 if (Counts.empty()) 0
1388 break; 0
1389 ----
1390 // Find the best candidate with respect to the number of extenders covered. ----
1391 auto BestIt = std::max_element(Counts.begin(), Counts.end(), 0
1392 [](const CMap::value_type &A, const CMap::value_type &B) { 0
1393 return A.second < B.second || 0
1394 (A.second == B.second && A < B); 0
1395 }); ----
1396 int32_t Best = BestIt->first; 0
1397 ExtValue BestV(ER, Best); 0
1398 for (RangeTree::Node *N : Tree.nodesWith(Best)) { 0
1399 for (unsigned I : RangeMap[N->Range]) 0
1400 IMap[{BestV,Extenders[I].Expr}].insert(I); 0
1401 Tree.erase(N); 0
1402 } 0
1403 } 0
1404 ----
1405 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "IMap (before fixup) = " << PrintIMap(IMap, *HRI)); 0
1406 ----
1407 // There is some ambiguity in what initializer should be used, if the ----
1408 // descriptor's subexpression is non-trivial: it can be the entire ----
1409 // subexpression (which is what has been done so far), or it can be ----
1410 // the extender's value itself, if all corresponding extenders have the ----
1411 // exact value of the initializer (i.e. require offset of 0). ----
1412 ----
1413 // To reduce the number of initializers, merge such special cases. ----
1414 for (std::pair &P : IMap) { 0
1415 // Skip trivial initializers. ----
1416 if (P.first.second.trivial()) 0
1417 continue; 0
1418 // If the corresponding trivial initializer does not exist, skip this ----
1419 // entry. ----
1420 const ExtValue &EV = P.first.first; 0
1421 AssignmentMap::iterator F = IMap.find({EV, ExtExpr()}); 0
1422 if (F == IMap.end()) 0
1423 continue; 0
1424 ----
1425 // Finally, check if all extenders have the same value as the initializer. ----
1426 // Make sure that extenders that are a part of a stack address are not ----
1427 // merged with those that aren't. Stack addresses need an offset field ----
1428 // (to be used by frame index elimination), while non-stack expressions ----
1429 // can be replaced with forms (such as rr) that do not have such a field. ----
1430 // Example: ----
1431 // ----
1432 // Collected 3 extenders ----
1433 // =2. imm:0 off:32968 bb#2: %7 = ## + __ << 0, def ----
1434 // 0. imm:0 off:267 bb#0: __ = ## + SS#1 << 0 ----
1435 // 1. imm:0 off:267 bb#1: __ = ## + SS#1 << 0 ----
1436 // Ranges ----
1437 // 0. [-756,267]a1+0 ----
1438 // 1. [-756,267]a1+0 ----
1439 // 2. [201,65735]a1+0 ----
1440 // RangeMap ----
1441 // [-756,267]a1+0 -> 0 1 ----
1442 // [201,65735]a1+0 -> 2 ----
1443 // IMap (before fixup) = { ----
1444 // [imm:0 off:267, ## + __ << 0] -> { 2 } ----
1445 // [imm:0 off:267, ## + SS#1 << 0] -> { 0 1 } ----
1446 // } ----
1447 // IMap (after fixup) = { ----
1448 // [imm:0 off:267, ## + __ << 0] -> { 2 0 1 } ----
1449 // [imm:0 off:267, ## + SS#1 << 0] -> { } ----
1450 // } ----
1451 // Inserted def in bb#0 for initializer: [imm:0 off:267, ## + __ << 0] ----
1452 // %12:intregs = A2_tfrsi 267 ----
1453 // ----
1454 // The result was ----
1455 // %12:intregs = A2_tfrsi 267 ----
1456 // S4_pstorerbt_rr %3, %12, %stack.1, 0, killed %4 ----
1457 // Which became ----
1458 // r0 = #267 ----
1459 // if (p0.new) memb(r0+r29<<#4) = r2 ----
1460 ----
1461 bool IsStack = any_of(F->second, [this](unsigned I) { 0
1462 return Extenders[I].Expr.Rs.isSlot(); 0
1463 }); ----
1464 auto SameValue = [&EV,this,IsStack](unsigned I) { 0
1465 const ExtDesc &ED = Extenders[I]; 0
1466 return ED.Expr.Rs.isSlot() == IsStack && 0
1467 ExtValue(ED).Offset == EV.Offset; 0
1468 }; 0
1469 if (all_of(P.second, SameValue)) { 0
1470 F->second.insert(P.second.begin(), P.second.end()); 0
1471 P.second.clear(); 0
1472 } ----
1473 } ----
1474 ----
1475 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "IMap (after fixup) = " << PrintIMap(IMap, *HRI)); 0
1476 } 0
1477 ----
1478 void HCE::calculatePlacement(const ExtenderInit &ExtI, const IndexList &Refs, 0
1479 LocDefList &Defs) { ----
1480 if (Refs.empty()) 0
1481 return; 0
1482 ----
1483 // The placement calculation is somewhat simple right now: it finds a ----
1484 // single location for the def that dominates all refs. Since this may ----
1485 // place the def far from the uses, producing several locations for ----
1486 // defs that collectively dominate all refs could be better. ----
1487 // For now only do the single one. ----
1488 DenseSet Blocks; 0
1489 DenseSet RefMIs; 0
1490 const ExtDesc &ED0 = Extenders[Refs[0]]; 0
1491 MachineBasicBlock *DomB = ED0.UseMI->getParent(); 0
1492 RefMIs.insert(ED0.UseMI); 0
1493 Blocks.insert(DomB); 0
1494 for (unsigned i = 1, e = Refs.size(); i != e; ++i) { 0
1495 const ExtDesc &ED = Extenders[Refs[i]]; 0
1496 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = ED.UseMI->getParent(); 0
1497 RefMIs.insert(ED.UseMI); 0
1498 DomB = MDT->findNearestCommonDominator(DomB, MBB); 0
1499 Blocks.insert(MBB); 0
1500 } ----
1501 ----
1502 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
1503 // The block DomB should be dominated by the def of each register used ----
1504 // in the initializer. ----
1505 Register Rs = ExtI.second.Rs; // Only one reg allowed now. 0
1506 const MachineInstr *DefI = Rs.isVReg() ? MRI->getVRegDef(Rs.Reg) : nullptr; 0
1507 ----
1508 // This should be guaranteed given that the entire expression is used ----
1509 // at each instruction in Refs. Add an assertion just in case. ----
1510 assert(!DefI || MDT->dominates(DefI->getParent(), DomB)); 0
1511 #endif ----
1512 ----
1513 MachineBasicBlock::iterator It; 0
1514 if (Blocks.count(DomB)) { 0
1515 // Try to find the latest possible location for the def. ----
1516 MachineBasicBlock::iterator End = DomB->end(); 0
1517 for (It = DomB->begin(); It != End; ++It) 0
1518 if (RefMIs.count(&*It)) 0
1519 break; 0
1520 assert(It != End && "Should have found a ref in DomB"); 0
1521 } else { ----
1522 // DomB does not contain any refs. ----
1523 It = DomB->getFirstTerminator(); 0
1524 } ----
1525 Loc DefLoc(DomB, It); 0
1526 Defs.emplace_back(DefLoc, Refs); 0
1527 } 0
1528 ----
1529 HCE::Register HCE::insertInitializer(Loc DefL, const ExtenderInit &ExtI) { 0
1530 llvm::Register DefR = MRI->createVirtualRegister(&Hexagon::IntRegsRegClass); 0
1531 MachineBasicBlock &MBB = *DefL.Block; 0
1532 MachineBasicBlock::iterator At = DefL.At; 0
1533 DebugLoc dl = DefL.Block->findDebugLoc(DefL.At); 0
1534 const ExtValue &EV = ExtI.first; 0
1535 MachineOperand ExtOp(EV); 0
1536 ----
1537 const ExtExpr &Ex = ExtI.second; 0
1538 const MachineInstr *InitI = nullptr; 0
1539 ----
1540 if (Ex.Rs.isSlot()) { 0
1541 assert(Ex.S == 0 && "Cannot have a shift of a stack slot"); 0
1542 assert(!Ex.Neg && "Cannot subtract a stack slot"); 0
1543 // DefR = PS_fi Rb,##EV ----
1544 InitI = BuildMI(MBB, At, dl, HII->get(Hexagon::PS_fi), DefR) 0
1545 .add(MachineOperand(Ex.Rs)) 0
1546 .add(ExtOp); 0
1547 } else { ----
1548 assert((Ex.Rs.Reg == 0 || Ex.Rs.isVReg()) && "Expecting virtual register"); 0
1549 if (Ex.trivial()) { 0
1550 // DefR = ##EV ----
1551 InitI = BuildMI(MBB, At, dl, HII->get(Hexagon::A2_tfrsi), DefR) 0
1552 .add(ExtOp); 0
1553 } else if (Ex.S == 0) { 0
1554 if (Ex.Neg) { 0
1555 // DefR = sub(##EV,Rb) ----
1556 InitI = BuildMI(MBB, At, dl, HII->get(Hexagon::A2_subri), DefR) 0
1557 .add(ExtOp) 0
1558 .add(MachineOperand(Ex.Rs)); 0
1559 } else { ----
1560 // DefR = add(Rb,##EV) ----
1561 InitI = BuildMI(MBB, At, dl, HII->get(Hexagon::A2_addi), DefR) 0
1562 .add(MachineOperand(Ex.Rs)) 0
1563 .add(ExtOp); 0
1564 } ----
1565 } else { ----
1566 if (HST->useCompound()) { 0
1567 unsigned NewOpc = Ex.Neg ? Hexagon::S4_subi_asl_ri 0
1568 : Hexagon::S4_addi_asl_ri; ----
1569 // DefR = add(##EV,asl(Rb,S)) ----
1570 InitI = BuildMI(MBB, At, dl, HII->get(NewOpc), DefR) 0
1571 .add(ExtOp) 0
1572 .add(MachineOperand(Ex.Rs)) 0
1573 .addImm(Ex.S); 0
1574 } else { ----
1575 // No compounds are available. It is not clear whether we should ----
1576 // even process such extenders where the initializer cannot be ----
1577 // a single instruction, but do it for now. ----
1578 llvm::Register TmpR = MRI->createVirtualRegister(&Hexagon::IntRegsRegClass); 0
1579 BuildMI(MBB, At, dl, HII->get(Hexagon::S2_asl_i_r), TmpR) 0
1580 .add(MachineOperand(Ex.Rs)) 0
1581 .addImm(Ex.S); 0
1582 if (Ex.Neg) 0
1583 InitI = BuildMI(MBB, At, dl, HII->get(Hexagon::A2_subri), DefR) 0
1584 .add(ExtOp) 0
1585 .add(MachineOperand(Register(TmpR, 0))); 0
1586 else ----
1587 InitI = BuildMI(MBB, At, dl, HII->get(Hexagon::A2_addi), DefR) 0
1588 .add(MachineOperand(Register(TmpR, 0))) 0
1589 .add(ExtOp); 0
1590 } ----
1591 } ----
1592 } ----
1593 ----
1594 assert(InitI); 0
1595 (void)InitI; ----
1596 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Inserted def in bb#" << MBB.getNumber() 0
1597 << " for initializer: " << PrintInit(ExtI, *HRI) << "\n " ----
1598 << *InitI); ----
1599 return { DefR, 0 }; 0
1600 } 0
1601 ----
1602 // Replace the extender at index Idx with the register ExtR. ----
1603 bool HCE::replaceInstrExact(const ExtDesc &ED, Register ExtR) { 0
1604 MachineInstr &MI = *ED.UseMI; 0
1605 MachineBasicBlock &MBB = *MI.getParent(); 0
1606 MachineBasicBlock::iterator At = MI.getIterator(); 0
1607 DebugLoc dl = MI.getDebugLoc(); 0
1608 unsigned ExtOpc = MI.getOpcode(); 0
1609 ----
1610 // With a few exceptions, direct replacement amounts to creating an ----
1611 // instruction with a corresponding register opcode, with all operands ----
1612 // the same, except for the register used in place of the extender. ----
1613 unsigned RegOpc = getDirectRegReplacement(ExtOpc); 0
1614 ----
1615 if (RegOpc == TargetOpcode::REG_SEQUENCE) { 0
1616 if (ExtOpc == Hexagon::A4_combineri) 0
1617 BuildMI(MBB, At, dl, HII->get(RegOpc)) 0
1618 .add(MI.getOperand(0)) 0
1619 .add(MI.getOperand(1)) 0
1620 .addImm(Hexagon::isub_hi) 0
1621 .add(MachineOperand(ExtR)) 0
1622 .addImm(Hexagon::isub_lo); 0
1623 else if (ExtOpc == Hexagon::A4_combineir) 0
1624 BuildMI(MBB, At, dl, HII->get(RegOpc)) 0
1625 .add(MI.getOperand(0)) 0
1626 .add(MachineOperand(ExtR)) 0
1627 .addImm(Hexagon::isub_hi) 0
1628 .add(MI.getOperand(2)) 0
1629 .addImm(Hexagon::isub_lo); 0
1630 else ----
1631 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected opcode became REG_SEQUENCE"); 0
1632 MBB.erase(MI); 0
1633 return true; 0
1634 } ----
1635 if (ExtOpc == Hexagon::C2_cmpgei || ExtOpc == Hexagon::C2_cmpgeui) { 0
1636 unsigned NewOpc = ExtOpc == Hexagon::C2_cmpgei ? Hexagon::C2_cmplt 0
1637 : Hexagon::C2_cmpltu; ----
1638 BuildMI(MBB, At, dl, HII->get(NewOpc)) 0
1639 .add(MI.getOperand(0)) 0
1640 .add(MachineOperand(ExtR)) 0
1641 .add(MI.getOperand(1)); 0
1642 MBB.erase(MI); 0
1643 return true; 0
1644 } ----
1645 ----
1646 if (RegOpc != 0) { 0
1647 MachineInstrBuilder MIB = BuildMI(MBB, At, dl, HII->get(RegOpc)); 0
1648 unsigned RegN = ED.OpNum; 0
1649 // Copy all operands except the one that has the extender. ----
1650 for (unsigned i = 0, e = MI.getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) { 0
1651 if (i != RegN) 0
1652 MIB.add(MI.getOperand(i)); 0
1653 else ----
1654 MIB.add(MachineOperand(ExtR)); 0
1655 } ----
1656 MIB.cloneMemRefs(MI); 0
1657 MBB.erase(MI); 0
1658 return true; 0
1659 } ----
1660 ----
1661 if (MI.mayLoadOrStore() && !isStoreImmediate(ExtOpc)) { 0
1662 // For memory instructions, there is an asymmetry in the addressing ----
1663 // modes. Addressing modes allowing extenders can be replaced with ----
1664 // addressing modes that use registers, but the order of operands ----
1665 // (or even their number) may be different. ----
1666 // Replacements: ----
1667 // BaseImmOffset (io) -> BaseRegOffset (rr) ----
1668 // BaseLongOffset (ur) -> BaseRegOffset (rr) ----
1669 unsigned RegOpc, Shift; ----
1670 unsigned AM = HII->getAddrMode(MI); 0
1671 if (AM == HexagonII::BaseImmOffset) { 0
1672 RegOpc = HII->changeAddrMode_io_rr(ExtOpc); 0
1673 Shift = 0; 0
1674 } else if (AM == HexagonII::BaseLongOffset) { 0
1675 // Loads: Rd = L4_loadri_ur Rs, S, ## ----
1676 // Stores: S4_storeri_ur Rs, S, ##, Rt ----
1677 RegOpc = HII->changeAddrMode_ur_rr(ExtOpc); 0
1678 Shift = MI.getOperand(MI.mayLoad() ? 2 : 1).getImm(); 0
1679 } else { ----
1680 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected addressing mode"); 0
1681 } ----
1682 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
1683 if (RegOpc == -1u) { 0
1684 dbgs() << "\nExtOpc: " << HII->getName(ExtOpc) << " has no rr version\n"; 0
1685 llvm_unreachable("No corresponding rr instruction"); 0
1686 } ----
1687 #endif ----
1688 ----
1689 unsigned BaseP, OffP; ----
1690 HII->getBaseAndOffsetPosition(MI, BaseP, OffP); 0
1691 ----
1692 // Build an rr instruction: (RegOff + RegBase<<0) ----
1693 MachineInstrBuilder MIB = BuildMI(MBB, At, dl, HII->get(RegOpc)); 0
1694 // First, add the def for loads. ----
1695 if (MI.mayLoad()) 0
1696 MIB.add(getLoadResultOp(MI)); 0
1697 // Handle possible predication. ----
1698 if (HII->isPredicated(MI)) 0
1699 MIB.add(getPredicateOp(MI)); 0
1700 // Build the address. ----
1701 MIB.add(MachineOperand(ExtR)); // RegOff 0
1702 MIB.add(MI.getOperand(BaseP)); // RegBase 0
1703 MIB.addImm(Shift); // << Shift 0
1704 // Add the stored value for stores. ----
1705 if (MI.mayStore()) 0
1706 MIB.add(getStoredValueOp(MI)); 0
1707 MIB.cloneMemRefs(MI); 0
1708 MBB.erase(MI); 0
1709 return true; 0
1710 } ----
1711 ----
1712 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
1713 dbgs() << '\n' << MI; 0
1714 #endif ----
1715 llvm_unreachable("Unhandled exact replacement"); 0
1716 return false; ----
1717 } 0
1718 ----
1719 // Replace the extender ED with a form corresponding to the initializer ExtI. ----
1720 bool HCE::replaceInstrExpr(const ExtDesc &ED, const ExtenderInit &ExtI, 0
1721 Register ExtR, int32_t &Diff) { ----
1722 MachineInstr &MI = *ED.UseMI; 0
1723 MachineBasicBlock &MBB = *MI.getParent(); 0
1724 MachineBasicBlock::iterator At = MI.getIterator(); 0
1725 DebugLoc dl = MI.getDebugLoc(); 0
1726 unsigned ExtOpc = MI.getOpcode(); 0
1727 ----
1728 if (ExtOpc == Hexagon::A2_tfrsi) { 0
1729 // A2_tfrsi is a special case: it's replaced with A2_addi, which introduces ----
1730 // another range. One range is the one that's common to all tfrsi's uses, ----
1731 // this one is the range of immediates in A2_addi. When calculating ranges, ----
1732 // the addi's 16-bit argument was included, so now we need to make it such ----
1733 // that the produced value is in the range for the uses alone. ----
1734 // Most of the time, simply adding Diff will make the addi produce exact ----
1735 // result, but if Diff is outside of the 16-bit range, some adjustment ----
1736 // will be needed. ----
1737 unsigned IdxOpc = getRegOffOpcode(ExtOpc); 0
1738 assert(IdxOpc == Hexagon::A2_addi); 0
1739 ----
1740 // Clamp Diff to the 16 bit range. ----
1741 int32_t D = isInt<16>(Diff) ? Diff : (Diff > 0 ? 32767 : -32768); 0
1742 if (Diff > 32767) { 0
1743 // Split Diff into two values: one that is close to min/max int16, ----
1744 // and the other being the rest, and such that both have the same ----
1745 // "alignment" as Diff. ----
1746 uint32_t UD = Diff; 0
1747 OffsetRange R = getOffsetRange(MI.getOperand(0)); 0
1748 uint32_t A = std::min(R.Align, 1u << llvm::countr_zero(UD)); 0
1749 D &= ~(A-1); 0
1750 } ----
1751 BuildMI(MBB, At, dl, HII->get(IdxOpc)) 0
1752 .add(MI.getOperand(0)) 0
1753 .add(MachineOperand(ExtR)) 0
1754 .addImm(D); 0
1755 Diff -= D; 0
1756 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
1757 // Make sure the output is within allowable range for uses. ----
1758 // "Diff" is a difference in the "opposite direction", i.e. Ext - DefV, ----
1759 // not DefV - Ext, as the getOffsetRange would calculate. ----
1760 OffsetRange Uses = getOffsetRange(MI.getOperand(0)); 0
1761 if (!Uses.contains(-Diff)) 0
1762 dbgs() << "Diff: " << -Diff << " out of range " << Uses 0
1763 << " for " << MI; 0
1764 assert(Uses.contains(-Diff)); 0
1765 #endif ----
1766 MBB.erase(MI); 0
1767 return true; 0
1768 } ----
1769 ----
1770 const ExtValue &EV = ExtI.first; (void)EV; 0
1771 const ExtExpr &Ex = ExtI.second; (void)Ex; 0
1772 ----
1773 if (ExtOpc == Hexagon::A2_addi || ExtOpc == Hexagon::A2_subri) { 0
1774 // If addi/subri are replaced with the exactly matching initializer, ----
1775 // they amount to COPY. ----
1776 // Check that the initializer is an exact match (for simplicity). ----
1777 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
1778 bool IsAddi = ExtOpc == Hexagon::A2_addi; 0
1779 const MachineOperand &RegOp = MI.getOperand(IsAddi ? 1 : 2); 0
1780 const MachineOperand &ImmOp = MI.getOperand(IsAddi ? 2 : 1); 0
1781 assert(Ex.Rs == RegOp && EV == ImmOp && Ex.Neg != IsAddi && 0
1782 "Initializer mismatch"); ----
1783 #endif ----
1784 BuildMI(MBB, At, dl, HII->get(TargetOpcode::COPY)) 0
1785 .add(MI.getOperand(0)) 0
1786 .add(MachineOperand(ExtR)); 0
1787 Diff = 0; 0
1788 MBB.erase(MI); 0
1789 return true; 0
1790 } ----
1791 if (ExtOpc == Hexagon::M2_accii || ExtOpc == Hexagon::M2_naccii || 0
1792 ExtOpc == Hexagon::S4_addaddi || ExtOpc == Hexagon::S4_subaddi) { 0
1793 // M2_accii: add(Rt,add(Rs,V)) (tied) ----
1794 // M2_naccii: sub(Rt,add(Rs,V)) ----
1795 // S4_addaddi: add(Rt,add(Rs,V)) ----
1796 // S4_subaddi: add(Rt,sub(V,Rs)) ----
1797 // Check that Rs and V match the initializer expression. The Rs+V is the ----
1798 // combination that is considered "subexpression" for V, although Rx+V ----
1799 // would also be valid. ----
1800 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
1801 bool IsSub = ExtOpc == Hexagon::S4_subaddi; 0
1802 Register Rs = MI.getOperand(IsSub ? 3 : 2); 0
1803 ExtValue V = MI.getOperand(IsSub ? 2 : 3); 0
1804 assert(EV == V && Rs == Ex.Rs && IsSub == Ex.Neg && "Initializer mismatch"); 0
1805 #endif ----
1806 unsigned NewOpc = ExtOpc == Hexagon::M2_naccii ? Hexagon::A2_sub 0
1807 : Hexagon::A2_add; ----
1808 BuildMI(MBB, At, dl, HII->get(NewOpc)) 0
1809 .add(MI.getOperand(0)) 0
1810 .add(MI.getOperand(1)) 0
1811 .add(MachineOperand(ExtR)); 0
1812 MBB.erase(MI); 0
1813 return true; 0
1814 } ----
1815 ----
1816 if (MI.mayLoadOrStore()) { 0
1817 unsigned IdxOpc = getRegOffOpcode(ExtOpc); 0
1818 assert(IdxOpc && "Expecting indexed opcode"); 0
1819 MachineInstrBuilder MIB = BuildMI(MBB, At, dl, HII->get(IdxOpc)); 0
1820 // Construct the new indexed instruction. ----
1821 // First, add the def for loads. ----
1822 if (MI.mayLoad()) 0
1823 MIB.add(getLoadResultOp(MI)); 0
1824 // Handle possible predication. ----
1825 if (HII->isPredicated(MI)) 0
1826 MIB.add(getPredicateOp(MI)); 0
1827 // Build the address. ----
1828 MIB.add(MachineOperand(ExtR)); 0
1829 MIB.addImm(Diff); 0
1830 // Add the stored value for stores. ----
1831 if (MI.mayStore()) 0
1832 MIB.add(getStoredValueOp(MI)); 0
1833 MIB.cloneMemRefs(MI); 0
1834 MBB.erase(MI); 0
1835 return true; 0
1836 } ----
1837 ----
1838 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
1839 dbgs() << '\n' << PrintInit(ExtI, *HRI) << " " << MI; 0
1840 #endif ----
1841 llvm_unreachable("Unhandled expr replacement"); 0
1842 return false; ----
1843 } 0
1844 ----
1845 bool HCE::replaceInstr(unsigned Idx, Register ExtR, const ExtenderInit &ExtI) { 0
1846 if (ReplaceLimit.getNumOccurrences()) { 0
1847 if (ReplaceLimit <= ReplaceCounter) 0
1848 return false; 0
1849 ++ReplaceCounter; 0
1850 } ----
1851 const ExtDesc &ED = Extenders[Idx]; 0
1852 assert((!ED.IsDef || ED.Rd.Reg != 0) && "Missing Rd for def"); 0
1853 const ExtValue &DefV = ExtI.first; 0
1854 assert(ExtRoot(ExtValue(ED)) == ExtRoot(DefV) && "Extender root mismatch"); 0
1855 const ExtExpr &DefEx = ExtI.second; 0
1856 ----
1857 ExtValue EV(ED); 0
1858 int32_t Diff = EV.Offset - DefV.Offset; 0
1859 const MachineInstr &MI = *ED.UseMI; 0
1860 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << __func__ << " Idx:" << Idx << " ExtR:" 0
1861 << PrintRegister(ExtR, *HRI) << " Diff:" << Diff << '\n'); ----
1862 ----
1863 // These two addressing modes must be converted into indexed forms ----
1864 // regardless of what the initializer looks like. ----
1865 bool IsAbs = false, IsAbsSet = false; 0
1866 if (MI.mayLoadOrStore()) { 0
1867 unsigned AM = HII->getAddrMode(MI); 0
1868 IsAbs = AM == HexagonII::Absolute; 0
1869 IsAbsSet = AM == HexagonII::AbsoluteSet; 0
1870 } ----
1871 ----
1872 // If it's a def, remember all operands that need to be updated. ----
1873 // If ED is a def, and Diff is not 0, then all uses of the register Rd ----
1874 // defined by ED must be in the form (Rd, imm), i.e. the immediate offset ----
1875 // must follow the Rd in the operand list. ----
1876 std::vector> RegOps; 0
1877 if (ED.IsDef && Diff != 0) { 0
1878 for (MachineOperand &Op : MRI->use_operands(ED.Rd.Reg)) { 0
1879 MachineInstr &UI = *Op.getParent(); 0
1880 RegOps.push_back({&UI, getOperandIndex(UI, Op)}); 0
1881 } ----
1882 } ----
1883 ----
1884 // Replace the instruction. ----
1885 bool Replaced = false; 0
1886 if (Diff == 0 && DefEx.trivial() && !IsAbs && !IsAbsSet) 0
1887 Replaced = replaceInstrExact(ED, ExtR); 0
1888 else ----
1889 Replaced = replaceInstrExpr(ED, ExtI, ExtR, Diff); 0
1890 ----
1891 if (Diff != 0 && Replaced && ED.IsDef) { 0
1892 // Update offsets of the def's uses. ----
1893 for (std::pair P : RegOps) { 0
1894 unsigned J = P.second; 0
1895 assert(P.first->getNumOperands() > J+1 && 0
1896 P.first->getOperand(J+1).isImm()); ----
1897 MachineOperand &ImmOp = P.first->getOperand(J+1); 0
1898 ImmOp.setImm(ImmOp.getImm() + Diff); 0
1899 } ----
1900 // If it was an absolute-set instruction, the "set" part has been removed. ----
1901 // ExtR will now be the register with the extended value, and since all ----
1902 // users of Rd have been updated, all that needs to be done is to replace ----
1903 // Rd with ExtR. ----
1904 if (IsAbsSet) { 0
1905 assert(ED.Rd.Sub == 0 && ExtR.Sub == 0); 0
1906 MRI->replaceRegWith(ED.Rd.Reg, ExtR.Reg); 0
1907 } ----
1908 } ----
1909 ----
1910 return Replaced; 0
1911 } 0
1912 ----
1913 bool HCE::replaceExtenders(const AssignmentMap &IMap) { 0
1914 LocDefList Defs; 0
1915 bool Changed = false; 0
1916 ----
1917 for (const std::pair &P : IMap) { 0
1918 const IndexList &Idxs = P.second; 0
1919 if (Idxs.size() < CountThreshold) 0
1920 continue; 0
1921 ----
1922 Defs.clear(); 0
1923 calculatePlacement(P.first, Idxs, Defs); 0
1924 for (const std::pair &Q : Defs) { 0
1925 Register DefR = insertInitializer(Q.first, P.first); 0
1926 NewRegs.push_back(DefR.Reg); 0
1927 for (unsigned I : Q.second) 0
1928 Changed |= replaceInstr(I, DefR, P.first); 0
1929 } ----
1930 } ----
1931 return Changed; 0
1932 } 0
1933 ----
1934 unsigned HCE::getOperandIndex(const MachineInstr &MI, 0
1935 const MachineOperand &Op) const { ----
1936 for (unsigned i = 0, n = MI.getNumOperands(); i != n; ++i) 0
1937 if (&MI.getOperand(i) == &Op) 0
1938 return i; 0
1939 llvm_unreachable("Not an operand of MI"); 0
1940 } ----
1941 ----
1942 const MachineOperand &HCE::getPredicateOp(const MachineInstr &MI) const { 0
1943 assert(HII->isPredicated(MI)); 0
1944 for (const MachineOperand &Op : MI.operands()) { 0
1945 if (!Op.isReg() || !Op.isUse() || 0
1946 MRI->getRegClass(Op.getReg()) != &Hexagon::PredRegsRegClass) 0
1947 continue; 0
1948 assert(Op.getSubReg() == 0 && "Predicate register with a subregister"); 0
1949 return Op; 0
1950 } ----
1951 llvm_unreachable("Predicate operand not found"); 0
1952 } ----
1953 ----
1954 const MachineOperand &HCE::getLoadResultOp(const MachineInstr &MI) const { 0
1955 assert(MI.mayLoad()); 0
1956 return MI.getOperand(0); 0
1957 } ----
1958 ----
1959 const MachineOperand &HCE::getStoredValueOp(const MachineInstr &MI) const { 0
1960 assert(MI.mayStore()); 0
1961 return MI.getOperand(MI.getNumExplicitOperands()-1); 0
1962 } ----
1963 ----
1964 bool HCE::runOnMachineFunction(MachineFunction &MF) { 0
1965 if (skipFunction(MF.getFunction())) 0
1966 return false; 0
1967 if (MF.getFunction().hasPersonalityFn()) { 0
1968 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << getPassName() << ": skipping " << MF.getName() 0
1969 << " due to exception handling\n"); ----
1970 return false; 0
1971 } ----
1972 LLVM_DEBUG(MF.print(dbgs() << "Before " << getPassName() << '\n', nullptr)); 0
1973 ----
1974 HST = &MF.getSubtarget(); 0
1975 HII = HST->getInstrInfo(); 0
1976 HRI = HST->getRegisterInfo(); 0
1977 MDT = &getAnalysis(); 0
1978 MRI = &MF.getRegInfo(); 0
1979 AssignmentMap IMap; 0
1980 ----
1981 collect(MF); 0
1982 llvm::sort(Extenders, [this](const ExtDesc &A, const ExtDesc &B) { 0
1983 ExtValue VA(A), VB(B); 0
1984 if (VA != VB) 0
1985 return VA < VB; 0
1986 const MachineInstr *MA = A.UseMI; 0
1987 const MachineInstr *MB = B.UseMI; 0
1988 if (MA == MB) { 0
1989 // If it's the same instruction, compare operand numbers. ----
1990 return A.OpNum < B.OpNum; 0
1991 } ----
1992 ----
1993 const MachineBasicBlock *BA = MA->getParent(); 0
1994 const MachineBasicBlock *BB = MB->getParent(); 0
1995 assert(BA->getNumber() != -1 && BB->getNumber() != -1); 0
1996 if (BA != BB) 0
1997 return BA->getNumber() < BB->getNumber(); 0
1998 return MDT->dominates(MA, MB); 0
1999 }); ----
2000 ----
2001 bool Changed = false; 0
2002 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Collected " << Extenders.size() << " extenders\n"); 0
2003 for (unsigned I = 0, E = Extenders.size(); I != E; ) { 0
2004 unsigned B = I; 0
2005 const ExtRoot &T = Extenders[B].getOp(); 0
2006 while (I != E && ExtRoot(Extenders[I].getOp()) == T) 0
2007 ++I; 0
2008 ----
2009 IMap.clear(); 0
2010 assignInits(T, B, I, IMap); 0
2011 Changed |= replaceExtenders(IMap); 0
2012 } ----
2013 ----
2014 LLVM_DEBUG({ 0
2015 if (Changed) ----
2016 MF.print(dbgs() << "After " << getPassName() << '\n', nullptr); ----
2017 else ----
2018 dbgs() << "No changes\n"; ----
2019 }); ----
2020 return Changed; 0
2021 } 0

46 assert(isPowerOf2_32(A)); 46 assert(isPowerOf2_32(A));
47 int32_t U = (V & -A) + O; 47 int32_t U = (V & -A) + O;

49 } 49 }

666 RangeTree::Node *RangeTree::rotateLeft(Node *Lower, Node *Higher) { 666 RangeTree::Node *RangeTree::rotateLeft(Node *Lower, Node *Higher) {
667 assert(Higher->Right == Lower); 667 assert(Higher->Right == Lower);
668 // The Lower node is on the right from Higher. Make sure that Lower's 668 // The Lower node is on the right from Higher. Make sure that Lower's

670 // an unbalanced tree again. 670 // an unbalanced tree again.

681 RangeTree::Node *RangeTree::rotateRight(Node *Lower, Node *Higher) { 681 RangeTree::Node *RangeTree::rotateRight(Node *Lower, Node *Higher) {
682 assert(Higher->Left == Lower); 682 assert(Higher->Left == Lower);
683 // The Lower node is on the left from Higher. Make sure that Lower's 683 // The Lower node is on the left from Higher. Make sure that Lower's
684 // balance is greater to the left. Otherwise the rotation will create 684 // balance is greater to the left. Otherwise the rotation will create
